# Built by dot-update.d/ollama as the `code` model - used via the `aider`
# wrapper function (.zshrc.d/aider), or directly with `ollama run code`.
#
# Same role as htpc's Modelfile.code (a Claude stand-in for when Claude
# itself isn't reachable), sized for this box's real ceiling: CPU-only,
# 2c/4t. This is the one that actually matters when there's no LAN either -
# htpc's qwen2.5-coder:14b needs the network; this is what's left without
# it. Weaker, but present.
#
# No SYSTEM block here - dot-update.d/ollama assembles it at build time from
# ~/.claude/context/{workbench,garden}.md (the same identity/approach layer
# every real Claude Code session gets via SessionStart hooks) plus
# code-system-addendum.md in this directory. Editing those source files and
# rerunning dot-update keeps this in sync automatically; editing SYSTEM here
# would do nothing, there isn't one. `offload` deliberately skips this -
# it's meant to be fast and low-stakes, and 150+ lines of philosophy on
# every quick call works against that.

FROM qwen2.5-coder:7b

PARAMETER temperature 0.2
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1
